# Redmine MCP Server

## Project Overview
This is an MCP (Model Context Protocol) server that bridges Cursor IDE with Redmine.
It allows AI to read Redmine tickets/requirements and manage git branches automatically.
Authentication uses **username/password** (HTTP Basic Auth), not API key.

## Tech Stack
- **Runtime:** Node.js >= 18 (portable Node v24 at `D:\Software\node-v24.11.0-win-x64\node-v24.11.0-win-x64`)
- **Language:** TypeScript (strict mode, ES2022, Node16 module)
- **Package type:** ESM (`"type": "module"` in package.json)
- **MCP SDK:** `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` — supports stdio and SSE transport
- **HTTP Server:** Express (for SSE transport mode)
- **HTTP Client:** Axios with Basic Auth
- **Linting:** ESLint (flat config) + Prettier
- **Git Hooks:** Husky + lint-staged

## Project Structure
```
├── index.ts              # MCP server entry — tool definitions & handlers
├── redmine-client.ts     # Redmine REST API client (Basic Auth)
├── git-helper.ts         # Git operations (create branch, list branches, etc.)
├── dist/                 # Compiled JS output (do not edit)
├── .env                  # Local credentials (never commit)
└── .env.example          # Template for .env
```

## Key Architecture Decisions
- Dual transport: **stdio** (default, Cursor local) or **SSE** (HTTP server with custom port for Docker/remote).
- `TRANSPORT=stdio` → Cursor spawns process, communicates via stdin/stdout.
- `TRANSPORT=sse` + `PORT=3000` → Express HTTP server, Cursor connects via `http://localhost:3000/sse`.
- `console.error()` for server logs (stdout is reserved for MCP protocol in stdio mode).
- All Redmine API calls go through `RedmineClient` class.
- All git operations go through `git-helper.ts` using `child_process.execSync`.

## Coding Conventions
- Use ES module imports with `.js` extension (required by Node16 module resolution).
- Keep imports at the top of every file — no inline imports.
- Use `interface` for data shapes, `type` for unions/intersections.
- Error handling: catch errors in tool handlers and return `{ isError: true }` with a descriptive message.
- Branch naming: `{prefix}/{issueId}-{slugified-title}` (e.g. `feature/1234-fix-login-bug`).

## Common Commands
```bash
npm run build          # Compile TypeScript
npm run start          # Run compiled server
npm run dev            # Run with auto-reload (nodemon + tsx)
npm run lint           # Run ESLint
npm run lint:fix       # Run ESLint with auto-fix
npm run format         # Run Prettier
npm run format:check   # Check Prettier formatting
```

## Environment Variables
| Variable | Required | Description |
|----------|----------|-------------|
| REDMINE_URL | Yes | Redmine base URL |
| REDMINE_USERNAME | Yes | Redmine login username |
| REDMINE_PASSWORD | Yes | Redmine login password |
| TRANSPORT | No | `stdio` (default) or `sse` |
| PORT | No | HTTP port when TRANSPORT=sse (default: 3000) |
| GIT_REPO_PATH | No | Default git repo path |
| BRANCH_FORMAT | No | `ticket-id` or `ticket-id-title` |

## Important Notes
- Never log to `console.log()` — it breaks MCP stdio protocol. Use `console.error()` only.
- The `.env` file contains credentials — never commit it.
- When adding new MCP tools, define them in `ListToolsRequestSchema` handler and implement in `CallToolRequestSchema` handler (both in `index.ts`).
